        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 2:18PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 218 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Matagorda Island State Park, or 9 miles south of Port Oconnor, moving
north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Port Oconnor, Point Comfort, Alamo Beach, Olivia, Indianola, Magnolia
Beach, Schicke Point, Port Alto, and Matagorda Island State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
